<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-106-414  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 106 414.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  August 1989 v6 n8 p101(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>What you ought to know about the SHELL.CFG file.andO;(SYSTEMS.CHK)(part 3) (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Liebing, Edward.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The SHELL.CFG file is a specialized text file that can be builtwithin the NETx.COM file with any ASCII text editor.andP;  It performsthe crucial function in Netware 386 applications programming oftransmitting configuration values to the user's workstation.andP;  Itsrange of options include cache buffers, file handles, printheaders, print tails and local printers.andP;  The remaining optionsinclude EOJ, HOLD, SHARE, LONG MACHINE TYPE, SHORT MACHINE, LOCKRETRIES, LOCK DELAY, READ COMPATIBILITY, SEARCH MODE, MAXIMUMTASKS, PATCH and TASK MODE.andP;  Each category is detailed.andO;Particular attention is given to the five potential settings ofthe SEARCH MODE, since the search mode entered in the SHELL.CFGfile will be applicable to all applications on a global basis.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    NOVL.andO;Product:   NetWare 386 (Network operating system) (usage).andO;Topic:     Network Operating SystemsApplications ProgrammingFile ManagementSystems SoftwareInformation Storage and RetrievalMS-DOS.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   List of available modes a program can use to find files on searchdrives. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>